This paper discusses methods for comparing impact factors and citation rates across fields of science, which is a topic that is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The use of the Science Citation Index and field categories suggests a focus on bibliometrics and information retrieval (cs.DL, cs.IR), while the comparison of normalization methods could also be relevant to topics such as social network analysis (cs.SI), cybersecurity (cs.CY), and cryptography (cs.CR).
